        <h1 style="text-align: center;"><em>what is RelocateGuru?</em></h1>
        <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 26px; font-family: futura-lt-w01-light, sans-serif;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">RelocateGuru is a new global social network to find, share and organise everything&nbsp;you need to know about&nbsp;</span></span><span style="background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: georgia, palatino, 'book antiqua', 'palatino linotype', serif; font-size: 26px;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; font-family: futura-lt-w01-light, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">your town in one place</span></span></p>
        <p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #2a2a2a; font-family: futura-lt-w01-light, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; letter-spacing: 1.600000023841858px; text-align: start;">I wished it wasn't so hard to feel at home when moving to a new place, and it wasn't just me finding it difficult. My friends would tell me their struggles and the headache it was trying to get settled in their new cities. From organising the logistics; from schools, houses and all the practical things, to&nbsp;finding friends and finding all the little things we take for granted and miss from&nbsp;home. And despite searching hundreds of websites, blogs and forum groups there was so much that I still didn't know until a neighbour told me months later something that would've been handy earlier.</span></p>
